    dc:description "FIG. 5. — Heteroscyphus aselliformis (Reinw., Blume & Nees) Schiffn.: A, leaf and underleaf; B, E, leaves; C, male bract with antheridium; D, G, H, underleaves; F, perianth; I, cells. All except F (from Guillaumin et Baumann-Bodenheim 12670 [PC0767993]) drawn from the following types of Chiloscyphus theriotii Steph.: A-D, H, from PC0767992; E, G, I, from G00069428. Scale bars: A, B, D-H, 1 mm; C, 500 µm; I, 50 µm." ;
